#+TITLE: Inner Product
#+context: linear algebra
* inner product                                                         :def:
* motivation
** The norm of a complex number $\lVert z \rVert$ should be non-negative, so we can define it as
   \[\begin{aligned}
   \lVert z \rVert =\sqrt{|z_1|^2 + \cdots + |z_n| ^2}
   \end{aligned}\]
   Since the square of the absolute value is just a complex number times a conjugate, and because 
